body.description: The SmartCompliance cabinet SmartTab ezRefill System is a simple but effective way for reordering and restocking, revolutionizing the replenishment process. It is quick, easy, and cost effective. As supplies are used, Smart Tab ezRefill reminder tabs notify you when it is time to reorder supplies and puts reorder information at your fingertips. The FAO SafetyHub, a mobile requisition app, also allows you to monitor cabinet usage to stay compliant and know when to reorder your refills. This large 50-person plastic SmartCompliance cabinet is perfect for industrial settings and large corporate offices. The unique cabinet design eliminates disorganized and missing supplies, while the clearly labeled compartments create a cabinet that is easy to use and restock. The expansion pocket allows you to customize your cabinet to meet your specific needs. The plastic case comes with a carrying handle. This large first aid cabinet can be mounted on a wall or other flat vertical surfaces.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Cabinet's handle breaks off
reviews.reviewText: This cabinet suppose to have a "break-away" handle, that should snap off when pulled and easily be replaced after. However, the handle just breaks off instead. This is our second office First Aid Cabinet that we purchased from this brand and the second one to break within months. We will have to look into getting a better quality product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, well made, won’t rust
reviews.reviewText: We bought this to put at our recreational pavilion on the beach. We live on an island in the Florida Keys, so everything rusts here. The plastic construction of this cabinet is sturdy and corrosion free. It’s mounted outside, so we really put it to the test. We’ve had ours about 9 months and had no issues with it at all. The kit is well organized and easy to understand with everything labeled and compartmented. Definitely recommended.
